tip.text: The flavours are gd, but pints have gotten more expensive, filled w/ more air & not to the brim. They've also begun selling bottled water. It's gone from a neighbourhood parlour to strictly business.
Every dish was a plate of salt. The smoked mackerel was underwhelming. The best dish was the deconstructed peanut butter tim tam, which was presented with a tim tam anyway.
One scoop of rice per taco, and the pork is almost a non-feature. Garlic fries might as well be called dried oregano fries. Don't come for the food.
